{"TopicId":205004,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Have you ever landed a Kerbal on its feet under personal chute?","CreatedByName":"Hotel26","CreatedById":139095,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-26T03:59:55Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Hotel26","CreatedById":139095,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-26T03:59:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve always wondered whether \u003Cu\u003Ea stand-up landing\u003C/u\u003E can be done.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf it is possible, what is the technique??\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(I now have a range of craft that use a self \u0022bail-out\u0022 operation for Kerbals to land safely, so I\u0027ve been performing a lot of landings under personal chute; which is why I now (finally) ask.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"antipro","CreatedById":173370,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-26T06:01:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224036313\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205004\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221632628795\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022139095\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Hotel26\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Hotel26 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve always wondered whether \u003Cu\u003Ea stand-up landing\u003C/u\u003E can be done.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf it is possible, what is the technique??\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan lang=\u0022en\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003Eyes, I just tried right now, without a particular technique, other than slowing down a few meters from the ground.\u003Cbr\u003E\nor maybe I didn\u0027t understand the question well..\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Hotel26","CreatedById":139095,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-26T06:08:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224036350\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205004\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221632636103\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022173370\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022antipro\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n19 minutes ago, antipro said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nor maybe I didn\u0027t understand the question well..\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy question was quite ambiguous but, after I had written it, I didn\u0027t know how to correct it...\u00A0 Sorry about that!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIRL an experienced jumper, using a \u0022sport parachute\u0022 (the type the Kerbals use) will very usually land on his or her feet -- and \u003Cstrong\u003Estay on foot.\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0 I.e. not tuck-and-roll (tumble), nor having then to get back up on one\u0027s feet and brush the dirt off.\u00A0 \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs I recall, those chutes had a typical flying speed of 35 mph.\u00A0 So the technique requires the jumper to \u0022flare\u0022 for the landing to kill most of the forward speed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can come very close to a touch-down, staying upright, \u003Cu\u003Ebut can never quite do it\u003C/u\u003E.\u00A0 The Kerbal always collapses in a heap and then has to get up.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-09-26T06:20:48Z\u0022 title=\u002209/26/2021 06:20  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 26, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by Hotel26\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"antipro","CreatedById":173370,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-26T06:51:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224036351\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205004\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221632636483\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022139095\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Hotel26\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n45 minutes ago, Hotel26 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\na \u0022sport parachute\u0022 (the type the Kerbals use)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI call that \u0022\u003Cspan lang=\u0022en\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003Eairfoil parachute\u0022 or \u0022\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003Eaerodynamic parachute\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u0022 or \u0022\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003Ewing parachute\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u0022.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224036351\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205004\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221632636483\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022139095\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Hotel26\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n45 minutes ago, Hotel26 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo the technique requires the jumper to \u0022flare\u0022 for the landing to kill most of the forward speed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nare you still talking about IRL? Cause I\u0027ve just seen a YT video where a guy landed by only \u003Cspan lang=\u0022en\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003Eacting on the strings, modifying the shape of the wing, without therefore having \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003Eto \u0022flare\u0022. ok maybe in the following video, the wind has helped him a bit, but I\u0027m quite sure it is possible to do it.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/9aWjjm1B3M4?start=76\u0026amp;feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224036351\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205004\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221632636483\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022139095\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Hotel26\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n45 minutes ago, Hotel26 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can come very close to a touch-down, staying upright, \u003Cu\u003Ebut can never quite do it\u003C/u\u003E.\u00A0 The Kerbal always collapses in a heap and then has to get up.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know what you mean, I never use parachutes in game or IRL, but if you turn 180\u00B0 or 360\u00B0 just before landing you can kill the speed without increase the altitude.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nthese are my last 3 tries: \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.dropbox.com/s/xuyrk72fd14ixbk/2021-09-26%2008-41-54_edit.mkv?dl=0\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.dropbox.com/s/xuyrk72fd14ixbk/2021-09-26 08-41-54_edit.mkv?dl=0\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-09-26T06:54:00Z\u0022 title=\u002209/26/2021 06:54  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 26, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by antipro\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Hotel26","CreatedById":139095,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-26T08:05:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224036359\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205004\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221632639071\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022173370\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022antipro\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, antipro said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthese are my last 3 tries\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s what I wanted: a very helpful existence proof!\u00A0 Thank you.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nConclusion: It Can Be Done.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Hotel26","CreatedById":139095,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-27T09:55:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224036359\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205004\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221632639071\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022173370\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022antipro\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 9/26/2021 at 2:51 PM, antipro said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthe wind has helped him a bit\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, compare with\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/nlxswZh-0jA?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKnowing that it can be done in KSP helps a lot (motivationally), but I still haven\u0027t pulled it off.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ll keep trying though.\u00A0 It seems all about horizontal motion \u0026lt; 1 m/s not more than about 1m or so above the ground.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-09-27T09:56:52Z\u0022 title=\u002209/27/2021 09:56  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 27, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by Hotel26\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}